NAME
	remove_dir - remove a directory

SYNOPSIS
	int remove_dir(string path)


DESCRIPTION
	Remove the directory named by path.  The path is first reduced to
	its minimal absolute form, with a relative path resolved against
	the current object's directory.  The return value is non-zero on
	success and zero if the directory could not be removed.

	The kernel layer wraps the raw operation in file security and
	resource accounting.  A successful removal returns one file block
	to the directory creator's quota, and runs with tick and stack
	accounting suspended.

ACCESS
	Unless the creator of the current object is "System", the current
	object must have write access to path.  No object may remove a
	directory under /kernel or /include/kernel.

ERRORS
	A path that fails the access rules above fails with "Access
	denied".  Calling remove_dir() with no current object fails with
	"Permission denied".

SEE ALSO
	efun/make_dir, efun/get_dir, kfun/remove_dir
